cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper investigates users' interaction with a humanoid robot in a real-time HRI experiment.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the study involves human participants interacting with a robot and evaluating their preferences for different communication modalities.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the study involves teaching a robot to imitate human actions.
- cs.SD (Sound) is a possible category as one of the interaction modalities tested was voice.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also possible as the study involves communication between humans and a robot through different modalities.
